@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Aye_Q" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Aye_Q runs fine
      on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with a
      68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To move a peg (a tile with rectangular shape on it), just click
on it with the mouse pointer and click on the empty space (a tile
with a small dot) where you want to move the peg. You can only move
a peg 2 spaces horizontally or vertically. If the move is possible,
the selected peg will go there.

  In 'Aye_Q' there are two ways to play:

 -The @{b}Normal@{ub} game:   You must jump over a @{b}peg@{ub} and that peg will be
                     removed.

 -The @{b}Inverted@{ub} game: You must jump over an @{b}empty space@{ub} and a peg
                     will appear there, just as if you would play
                     the 'Normal' game backward.

  The goal of the game is to remove all the pegs (or fill up the
board, if the game is inverted), until only one peg is left (or
only one space is empty, in the inverted game), preferably in the
center, where the empty space (or peg) was at the start.

  When there are no possible moves, the game ends and Aye_Q will
display how many pegs (or empty spaces for the 'Inverted' game) are
remaining.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS
-------

  At the right of the game board, the following buttons are shown:

 -@{b}New Game@{ub}:             Restarts the game.

 -@{b}About@{ub}:                Displays the informations about the game.

 -@{b}Normal/Inverted Game@{ub}: This is a toggle button between the 'Normal'
                        and the 'Inverted' game.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the main window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

